4.13 What type of repetition would be appropriate for obtaining an input from the user until the
user indicates there is no more input to provide? What type would be appropriate for calculating
the factorial of 5? Briefly describe how each of these tasks could be performed.

ANSWER
For indefinite input from user, Sentinel-controlled iteration is appropriate. Because the number of iterations is unknown before the loop starts, a sentinel value is used to end the loop

For definite iteration like factorial of 5, the counter-controlled iteration is appropriate. Because the number of iterations is known before the loop starts. i.e the loop willl run 5 times
